/*!
\page cmake-policies-qml.html
\title CMake Policies for QML
\brief Overview of CMake policies affecting QML module behavior

Qt Qml provides several CMake policies to control backward compatibility and behavior
of QML-related CMake commands.

\section1 Available Policies

\list
\li \l{QTP0001} - Controls QML module versioning behavior
\li \l{QTP0004} - Controls QML module output directory structure
\li \l{QTP0005} - Controls QML type registration behavior
\endlist

\section1 Setting Policies

Use \c{qt_policy()} or \c{cmake_policy()} to set these policies in your CMakeLists.txt:

\code
qt_policy(SET QTP0001 NEW)
\endcode

\sa {CMake Integration for QML}, {qt_add_qml_module}
*/
